##Chrome Comparison

To test it out, I went to a [random Forbes article](https://www.forbes.com/sites/catescottcampbell/2017/05/08/the-limit-does-not-exist-creative-brainpower-and-badass-women-in-stem/#370283616e63) and watched the network impact (hit F12, go to Network tab) as the page loaded on my wired 60mpbs connection.
I did not scroll or click anything on the page, and had cache disabled (so subsequent views wouldn't be sped up).
The longer and more frequent the bars, the more data is loaded into the page.
